article.headline: Indiana St. 66, Oakland City 52
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Marico Stinson scored 18 points to lead Indiana State to a 66-52 victory Monday night over Oakland City. The Mighty Oaks opened up a five-point lead early in the first half, but Indiana State (4-1) recovered to take a 32-29 halftime advantage. The Sycamores dominated underneath the basket with a 42-24 rebounding advantage -- grabbing 16 offensive rebounds while holding Oakland City to just two. Jay Tunnell and Trent Wurtz each had eight rebounds for the Sycamores, who had a 19-3 advantage on second-chance points. Chad Miller led the Oaks (2-3) with 13 points, followed by Keegan Carmony with 11 and Kyle Atterbury with 10. Indiana State's Gabe Moore added 15 points, while Tunnell had 13 points and Wurtz scored 10.
